headline: Why Analysts Say NetApp’s Story Is Shifting After Latest Results and Analyst Revisions
summary: NetApp's consensus analyst price target has nudged higher, rising from $119.71 to $121.14 per share. This modest increase reflects recent shifts in market sentiment, amid cautiously optimistic analyst commentary, continuing confidence in cloud software performance, and signs of steadier enterprise hardware demand. Stay tuned to discover how investors and stakeholders can follow the evolving NetApp narrative as new developments arise. What Wall Street Has Been Saying Analyst coverage of NetApp...
